OL,7,Fheard that Rickards stabbed her
OL,8,Fhusband five times, and kept his body
OL,9,Fin a cupboard in her room.
OL,11,FLater, she put his body in a bag and
OL,12,Fdragged it down the stairs into the
OL,13,Fgarden.
OL,15,FRickards had arranged for the garden
OL,16,Fto be tidied up and used the grass
OL,17,Fcuttings and leaves to cover the bag
OL,18,Fand leave his body to decompose.
OL,20,FWhen arrested, Maureen kept up the
OL,21,Fact, asking "what body?"
